Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Thinly slice @sweet Italian pork sausage{9%oz} into rounds.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until browned, ~{2-4%minutes} total. Remove from pot and set aside. Add onion, @garlic powder{2%tsp}, and @dried oregano{1%tsp} to pot. Cook, tossing, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Return sausage to pot, along with @crushed tomatoes{2%14oz boxes}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{}(5 cups). Stir, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot. Bring to a boil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once soup is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz}. Let cook until tender, about ~{8%minutes}.

Stir @spinach{5%oz} and @parsley{1/4%oz} into pot and let wilt. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} and @chili flakes{1%tsp}(to taste).

> You might want to skip the chili flakes for the kids.